e. I really need concrete evidence to justify any additional setup.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test setup requirements**\\n\\nI’m parsing the setup options for my test dependencies, which can be an extra Maven dependency, Docker image needs, or environment properties. I need to determine if the library requires setup beyond the usual test scaffold for meaningful coverage. For example, if a database client is involved, it needs a database, and generated scaffolding without Docker won’t cover its APIs effectively. I should also consider whether the extra setup is essential or merely nice-to-have, especially concerning the Java driver and its connection requirements.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Testcontainers usage**\\n\\nI’m determining the server requirements for behavior beyond object construction. The POM file includes Testcontainers for Neo4j, and I’m leaning toward suggesting careful preparation, factoring in potential risks. I’m questioning whether extra optional dependencies are necessary. It seems like the Testcontainers dependency might not be needed if the driver can initiate Docker through TCK, although deterministic images require code for container management. I should check if existing tests incorporate TCK test support, and clarify if we really need the org.testcontainers:neo4j dependency.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_R0XZYdLeQleQLkiNtR2G1gL8|fc_0583956590347f66016a4257b657248193bad175485f457de0", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"docker_image|Testcontainers|Neo4jContainer|withEnv\\(|testImplementation.*testcontainers|allowedDockerImages|dockerImages|DockerImage\" tests/src metadata buildSrc tck-build-logic forge -g '*.gradle' -g '*.java' -g '*.groovy' -g '*.json' -g '*.py' | head -200", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 278, "output": 949, "cacheRead": 42496, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43723, "cos