visory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The artifact can be partially exercised offline through Value/object-mapping APIs, but the documented core Neo4j Java Driver workflow requires a running Neo4j database for connectivity, sessions, and query execution; the upstream artifact also has Testcontainers Neo4j test dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"docker_image\",\n      \"image\": \"neo4j:5.26.0\",\n      \"slug\": \"neo4j-5-26-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Neo4j Java Driver 5.28.x is documented as compatible with Neo4j 5.x, and meaningful Driver/Session/query coverage requires a running Neo4j server over Bolt.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For tests that exercise Driver, Session, verifyConnectivity, executableQuery, or transaction paths, start the database container from test code with either authentication disabled via NEO4J_AUTH=none and AuthTokens.none(), or a known username/password and AuthTokens.basic(...). Publish Bolt port 7687 to a free localhost port, wait until Bolt accepts connections before creating the Driver, and avoid relying on external Aura credentials. Offline Value.as(...), Record.as(...), Config, and AuthTokens tests remain useful and should be kept for reachability-specific coverage.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The current Java-run failure shown in the issue is in an offline object-mapping test, so Docker may not be needed to fix that specific failing assertion.\",\n    \"Starting a database container increases test time and may add readiness/flakiness issues if the test does not wait for Bolt availability.\",\n    \"A new allowed Docker image may still be rejected by the repository's Docker image vulnerability policy during local or CI verification.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0583956590347f66016a4257cfcb6481938fde1f4398faf3fd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 793, "output": 1049, "cacheRead": 52224, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54066, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782732738888, "responseId": "resp_0583956590347f66016a4257c39ba48193b1bfa4001c67ec4b"}}
